DIY crease-easing spray for clothes

Who hasn’t wished for a completely wrinkle-free wardrobe! Try out this easy-to-make crease-release spray to keep your clothes looking impeccably unwrinkled. Mix ½ cup of white vinegar, one cup water and a few drops of lavender essential oil in a clean spray bottle. You may even use 1/4th cup of liquid fabric softener in place of the vinegar. Spritz the mixture on slightly damp but not wet clothes, gently tug or shake the fabric and hang to dry—the wrinkles will be gone.
